1. Install Docker

2. Create a Project Directory:
Open the Command Prompt (CMD) or terminal>>>>>>
mkdir my-web-app
cd my-web-app

3. Create server.js File (Web Application):
Run this command to create the server.js file:>>>>>>
notepad server.js

In the Notepad window that opens, paste the following code:>>>>>>
const http = require('http');

const hostname = '0.0.0.0';
const port = 3000;

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
    res.statusCode = 200;
    res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/plain');
    res.end('Hello, Docker!');
});

server.listen(port, hostname, () => {
    console.log(`Server running at http://${hostname}:${port}/`);
});

Save the file and close Notepad.


5. Create a Dockerfile (Docker Image Instructions):

Run this command to create the Dockerfile:>>>>>>
notepad Dockerfile

In the Notepad window that opens, paste the following content:>>>>>>
# Use an official Node.js image from Docker Hub
FROM node:14

# Create and set the working directory inside the container
WORKDIR /usr/src/app

# Copy package.json and package-lock.json into the container
COPY package*.json ./

# Install the dependencies inside the container
RUN npm install

# Copy the rest of the application code into the container
COPY . .

# Expose port 3000 on the container to the host machine
EXPOSE 3000

# Start the application
CMD ["node", "server.js"]

Save the file and close Notepad.

6. Build the Docker Image:
Ensure you're still in the my-web-app directory.
Run the following command to build the Docker image:>>>>>>
docker build -t my-web-app .


7. Run the Docker Container:>>>>>>
docker run -p 3000:3000 my-web-app

8. Test the Web Application:
Open a browser and go to http://localhost:3000, or use the following curl command to test it in the terminal:>>>>>>
curl http://localhost:3000

You should see the message Hello, Docker! displayed.

10. Stop the Running Container:
If you want to stop the container, press CTRL + C in the terminal where the container is running.>>>>> OR BY USING THIS COMMAND IF NOT WORK TO STOP
docker stop <container-id>



